HWComposer2 Integration Guide
=============================

Structure
=========
          +--------------------------------+
          |                                |
          |          Module Entry          |
          +--------------------------------+
                          |
                          V
          +--------------------------------+
          |            Basic hwc2          |
          |         (hwc2_common.h)        |
          +--------------------------------+
                              |
                              V
                  +------------------------+
                  |        Blitter         |
                  |    (hwc2_blitter.h)    |
                  +------------------------+

hwc2_common.h hwc2_common.cpp

Includes a basic hwc2 implemention, with blitter support but not enabled,
and without display features.
Soc-Vendor can use functions exported in hwc2_common.h


hwc2_blitter.cpp hwc2_blitter.h

Implements the blitter features, referenced by hwc2_common.cpp.
Soc-Vendor should not change them, either do not need to include the header
file.


hwc2_fbdev.cpp

Module entry, defines the module and device.
This is a reference.


Required Functions
==================

NOTICE that some function requires taking effect immediately upon
function returns. Must override the default function, ie implement practical
functionalities for such descriptors.

Such functions are listed below, see hwc2_common.h for more information.
  HWC2_FUNCTION_PRESENT_DISPLAY
  HWC2_FUNCTION_SET_ACTIVE_CONFIG
  HWC2_FUNCTION_SET_COLOR_MODE
  HWC2_FUNCTION_SET_POWER_MODE
  HWC2_FUNCTION_CREATE_VIRTUAL_DISPLAY
  HWC2_FUNCTION_DESTROY_VIRTUAL_DISPLAY
  HWC2_FUNCTION_REGISTER_CALLBACK
  HWC2_FUNCTION_CREATE_LAYER
  HWC2_FUNCTION_DESTROY_LAYER
  HWC2_FUNCTION_GET_CLIENT_TARGET_SUPPORT
  HWC2_FUNCTION_SET_VSYNC_ENABLED
  HWC2_FUNCTION_VALIDATE_DISPLAY
  HWC2_FUNCTION_SET_CURSOR_POSITION


